A man believed to be in his 50s sustained multiple gunshot wounds when he was hijacked in the driveway of his home in Boksburg on the East Rand on Monday. &#8220;Reports from the scene indicate the incident happened on Blinkblaar Street in Van Dyk Park,&#8221; said Netcare 911&#8217;s Athlenda Mathe. The exact detail as to what happened will form part of a police investigation. The man, who is in a serious condition, was stabilised on the scene and thereafter transported to a nearby hospital under the constant care of a Netcare 911 advanced life support paramedic. &#8211; Caxton News Service For more news your way, follow The Citizen on Facebook and Twitter .